               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18421212-name-633" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18421212-name-633" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421212-name-633" type="surname" value="PIGGOTT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421212-name-633" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES PIGGOTT</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Redcross-street, in the parish of St. Saviour's, Southwark. Last Sunday I left my house about twelve o'clock, with my wife, leaving it in care of a lodger—we returned about ten minutes past eight o'clock in the evening, and as my wife was going to put the key in the door three men rushed out on her, and nearly knocked her down—I caught told of the prisoner, who was one of them, and held him till the policeman came up, who found nine spoons in his pocket, seven of mine, and two of my lodger's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What became of the other two? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> They ran away—I cannot say whether they were older than the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18421212-name-634" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18421212-name-634" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421212-name-634" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421212-name-634" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH ROBINSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I lodge with Mr. Piggott. They went out between twelve and one o'clock—I went out at half-past six with my husband—I am sure I left the door quite fast—we came home between ten and eleven—I found that two of my spoons were gone, and a watch and three coats were packed up ready to go—the drawers were all opened, and ransacked—I lost about 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. worth of property.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did you try the door so as to be sure it was fast<lb></lb>ened? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—we were the last persons that left the house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18421212-name-635" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18421212-name-635" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
